	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Kinshasa - At least 27 people have died and 54 are missing after a boat sank in the river Kasai in the Democratic Republic of Congo, a local official said Sunday. "Rigorous" checks had confirmed "at this stage" the numbers of dead and missing in the accident, which happened overnight Thursday to Friday, the administrator of Idiofa territory, Jacques Mbila, told AFP. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  